“Its all one blood, don't care about your face
The color of your eye
Or the tone of your skin
Don't care where you are
Don't care where you been
'Cause where we gonna go
Is where we wanna be
The place where the little language is unity..”

node.text: At the end of the day we will offload our cameras to organize and watch our footage. It’s always such a fun joy seeing what special moments we missed that the cameras captured. WE HAD NO IDEA this even happened to @manillagee. He literally picked himself up and jumped back on the horse (after emptying the sand from his trunks and meeting a friendly pup;) 😅🐶😍

node.text: FAMILY MOVIE NIGHT watching #YouvsWild on @netflixfamily! 🦁🐒🦁 We embarked on an at-home mission to watch the new interactive movie "Animals on the Loose"! With family-friendly choices around every corner, we guided @beargrylls through his adventures as he wrangled the animals back to safety while we called the shots from the comfort of our living room. Stream and play along now, only on @Netflix, and show us how you're watching with your family using #YouvsWild 🗺️

node.text: This moment brought me to tears.. 🥲😍🥲 Cali saw this little boy playing with some rocks and started to give him some rocks he found, almost like a peace offering to friends.. ❤️💙💚 If you swipe through these photos you can see this very special moment when the boy was curious of Cali’s unique hair. Cali brings up his hands like, “what kind of greeting are we doing here?” And then they put their hands together and just stared at the differences AND THE SIMILARITIES..💚🌍💚 @caligee @thebucketlistfamily

node.text:
You know the phrase “Monkey see monkey do”..? How about, “Elephants see Dorothy do”..!? 🐘🥰🐘
Want to come to this amazing place with your family or friends? Are you a Bucket List Friend? That’s the name of our monthly email subscription that includes our monthly podcast video and an exclusive travel deal. This next month’s is a crazy amazing deal to this place! Check it out and sign up on our website thebucketlistfamily.com/friends ❤️💙💚

node.text: GIRLS TURN!! 😩😱😅 Once again, another example of a parent TRYING to put on a brave face for their child!! Can you hear what Dorothy says at the very end?? 😳

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by The Bucket List Family on July 12, 2021 tagging @garrettgee, @jessgee, @dorothygee, @manillagee, @thebucketlistfamily, @matetsivictoriafalls, and @caligee. May be an image of 5 people, people standing and outdoors.

node.text:
There are some ups AND downs to traveling right now : 1 of the downs is how tricky logistics have become due to Covid testing most every time we switch a country or destination. BUT the ups have far outweighed the downs! Perhaps the biggest up so far has been seeing just how much it means to the countries and lodges and tour companies to be open again. Most of our stops thus far we have been their 1st guests since reopening. They are thrilled and just so grateful to be open again. We love to travel because the positive effect it has on our kids and family..BUT so grateful when we can return the favor and be a source of some good to the places we visit as well.. 😌❤️🌎💚🥰
/// @matetsivictoriafalls

node.text: Do you see it in the background?? 🐘 I’m so grateful to be here, on safari, in the bush, seeing these magnificent animals in their wild habitat. We just arrived at the beautiful @matetsivictoriafalls in Zimbabwe 🇿🇼. You can see in our Instagram stories today that the moment our safari jeep left the camp to explore for animals Garrett says, “You’re in your happy place right now..” and right then I begin to cry.. 😭🥰😭

“Its all one blood, don't care about your face
The color of your eye
Or the tone of your skin
Don't care where you are
Don't care where you been
'Cause where we gonna go
Is where we wanna be
The place where the little language is unity..”
❤️💙💚
